TaskEncoder

This is one beginners often find confusing.

Suppose you have

task = Task(...)

Python's JSON module cannot do

json.dump(task)

because it doesn't know what a Task is.

So

TaskEncoder

teaches JSON.

It says

If you see a Task...

convert it into a dictionary.

Like

Task

↓

{
    "title":"Study",
    "priority":2,
    ...
}
dict
task.__dict__

returns

{
"title":...
"description":...
"priority":...
}

It's basically

"Give me every variable inside this object."

TaskDecoder

This performs the reverse.

JSON looks like

{
"title":"Study",
"priority":2
}

The decoder says

"Turn this back into a real Task object."

update_task
