One thing many beginners misunderstand

Notice that almost every modifying function calls save().

For example:

add_task()

↓

save()
update_task()

↓

save()
delete_task()

↓

save()

This means the application follows a simple strategy:

Every change is immediately written to disk.

There is no "Save" button.

If you delete a task, it's already gone from the file.

